name: Painting With a Twist
directions: At the back of the studio
comment: You may need to be a paying customer at night, but if you do during daytime hours and just ask the manager a few questions about the business, there will be no problem. Staff is friendly and tolerant.

name: Toups Meatery
directions: At the very back, past the kitchen.
comment: You may have to buy something, though you could probably sneak in easily during busy meal times.

name: Painting With a Twist
directions: There are two - ask when you go in.
comment: In the evening, you may need to be a paying customer, but in the daytime, you can go in and just ask a few questions about the place. People who work there are progressive artists, and are tolerant and kind.

name: Humanisten
directions: By the café.

name: Herbert Art Gallery and Museum
directions: On the first floor

name: Trident Booksellers and Cafe
directions: Downstairs in the back of the bookstore to the right are single-stall gendered bathrooms. There are additional bathrooms on the second floor: gendered stalls, and one (often immaculate, seldom used) gender neutral single stall all the way in the back, past both other bathrooms.
comment: They are pretty good about letting non-customers use their bathroom, but please consider supporting your local independent bookstore! :)

name: T. Maccarone's
directions: Through the restaurant, by the bar.
comment: No restrictions

name: University of Pittsburgh
directions: https://www.studentaffairs.pitt.edu/lgbtqia/single-occupancy-restrooms/
comment: The University has a full map of all single-user and gender neutral stalls on campus. See link.

name: Exiles Bar
directions: Single stall bathrooms on the first and second floors, located towards the back
comment: Take advantage of the crowd and slip through if you're not planning on getting a drink.

name: FringeArts/La Peg
directions: Next to the entrance to the theatre.
comment: I have used the restrooms at FringeArts when attending shows. There are men's and women's restrooms, and both have signs indicating that guests should use whichever facility they identify with. Same restrooms available for La Peg, the bar/restraunt on site.

name: Marshalls
directions: Left hand side of store, midway back in mens furnishings area
comment: Two gender neutral private restrooms

name: All Souls Unitarian Universalist Congregation
directions: Towards the back right of the main lobby.

name: Boston College - O'Neil Library
directions: On the ground level, go past the reception desk on your left and then make a left. It will be on your left.
comment: The address above is not exact; here is a map link: https://www.google.com/maps/place/Thomas+P+O'Neill+Jr+Library/@42.334988,-71.1713155,17z/data=!3m1!5s0x89e378609ad650b9:0x53f46861fab0a687!4m8!1m2!2m1!1sboston+college+oneil+library!3m4!1s0x89e3785da725d4c9:0xab72866c776bf06a!8m2!3d42.336119!4d-71.1691543

name: Palace Cinema
directions: Right next to the ticket taker inside the paid space.
comment: Literally the only single stall in the building. Also the only changing table for the theater, there is usually a line.

name: Molly Darcy's
directions: Through the back room to the right of the dance floor and bar. There are two single "stalls"/"bathrooms" (separate rooms). Both rooms are marked as male AND female. Anyone can use either.

name: Boston College - Murray Graduate Student House
directions: One right in front of you if you enter through the front door, another if you go up the stairs and turn right (it'll be on your right)
comment: It's technically a building for graduate students but no one ever checks. The most they'll do is say hi, if you run into anyone. This is their website: http://www.bc.edu/offices/gsc/mgc.html

name: Reynolds Journalism Institute
comment: urinals and standard toilets in womens room

name: Community Legal Services
directions: One on each side of first floor lobby. Single user and gender neutral.

name: Department of Anthropology/Department of Art History & Archaeology
directions: Third floor, south side of the building. Two separate All-Gender, one stall bathrooms. Elevator on the north side of the building for handicap accessibility.

name: Sproul Hall
directions: Two accessible, single stall, gender neutral restrooms are on the main floor of the building. One is next to the kitchen near the rear door. One is in the office area of the Communications department. There is an accessible entrance to the building's main floor.

name: Ritz Theatre
directions: In lobby. Handicapped/family restroom, but all can use.
comment: Theatre open to public Tuesday through Friday 9-5

name: Femoyer Hall, Blacksburg, VA 24060, USA
directions: First floor; facing the building, walk in, pass the door to the University Studies office, first right. It will be on your right.
comment: Academic building on the Virginia Tech campus.

name: Spoon Market
directions: When you go in to spoon it is a lot to take in but you are welcome there. just is one of the hosts and they can point you in the right direction. Otherwise it is all the way in the back (but before the staircase) on your left behind a privacy wall are two single stall  restrooms for you to choose from. They are clean and actually just as nice as the rest of this market/sanwich shop.
comment: I suggest browsing and maybe grabbing a coffee/tea or even water? Just in case but this is the place I go to edit photos and drink loads of coffee so they're really laid back. Owners are always there and are great people.

name: Ferguson Hall, University of MN West Bank
directions: Basement of building, by room 94, the far south-ish side of the building. They are tucked behind the corner that has the drinking fountain.
comment: Two single stall rooms, one accessible.

name: Olde Main Street Pub
directions: To the left of the bar.
comment: There are both gendered and a unisex/handicapped restroom. Did not remember to check if the gendered restrooms were also single stalled, but I would not be surprised if that were the case given their apparent sizes.

name: The Diamond Bar
directions: Passed the bar and the the right.
comment: Friendly neighborhood beer bar.

name: 53rd Street Branch, New York Public Library
directions: Two floors down on the teen/children's floor. Labelled "family restroom."
comment: If ANYONE tries to tell you you cannot use this restroom, find a librarian immediately. There should be one posted at the desk in the children's room.

name: Marcy's Bar & Lounge
comment: All inclusive bar. The restrooms are labeled with genders but are single use and considered unisex by bar staff and patrons.

name: Linda's Bar and Grill
directions: Upstairs or downstairs, head straight toward the back of the building.

name: Atomic Empire
directions: All the way in the back of the store.
comment: Not sure if bathrooms are accessible or not.

name: Mattie B's Public House
directions: Take a left coming in the main door and go down a short hallway near the soda fountain.
comment: Not certain if accessible, but they look like they might be.

name: Reno Bike Project
directions: Straight back from the entrance, red door.
comment: Our restroom isn't the nicest or cleanest, but it is available to the public.

name: Brunswick Library
directions: Restrooms are located in the main hallway.
comment: You'll need to get a key at the circulation desk.

name: Brunswick Stewdio
comment: Just let us know you need a safe bathroom. We are open Thurs/Fri/Sat from noon until 5:00.

name: Johnny Doughnuts
directions: Back behind the kitchen
comment: Probably have to be a customer, open 7am-2pm every day

name: Spike's Coffees & Teas
directions: ask to use it and you'll be directed behind the counter and out the back door to a unique single-stall bathroom for people of all genders
comment: prefer you're a paying customer, but staff are very kind

name: Spike's Coffees & Teas
directions: ask to use it and you'll be directed behind the counter and out the back to door to a unique single-stall bathroom for people of all genders
comment: prefer you're a paying customer, but staff are very kind

name: Beachside Cafe
directions: In the back behind the bookcase
comment: You may have to be a customer to access

name: Driver's Market
directions: In the back to the right of the refrigerated section
comment: Employees will direct you regardless of whether you're a paying customer

name: St. Paul's United Methodist Church
directions: Main floor, straight back from the main entrance there are two single room locking restrooms.

name: Belltown Pizza
comment: Very friendly staff.

name: Kathleen's Tea Room
comment: You should probably be a paying customer, but if you ask at the counter they're nice and are likely to not take issue.

name: La Cabana Restaurant
comment: They would probably let you use it without purchasing, but it would be more courteous to be a customer. Plus, their Ecuadorian food is fabulous. If you do eat here, order from the buffet. They're open all day.

name: Peekskill Coffee House
comment: The keys are hanging on hooks to the left of the food display case and register. You don't have to make purchases to use the stalls.

name: Central Lutheran Church
directions: We have two single stall gender neutral bathrooms in our building as well as safe gendered bathrooms.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Direct line from the door, where the two wine shelves meet.
comment: The company has an active anti discrimination policy on the bases of gender or sexual orientation, thus the store climate is  is safe.

name: Boston Public Library Children's Room
directions: In the Johnson building (most easily accessible from the door on Boylston Street) on the second floor, the newly renovated children's room has "family" bathroom spaces not designated by gender.

name: Literati Bookstore, East Washington Street, Ann Arbor, MI, United States
directions: Upstairs to the right of the coffee stand
comment: Upstairs is the coffeeshop, Downstairs is the bookstore so no purchase necessary

name: Apartment 50- Haverford Music and Arts House
directions: Upstairs off any of the four common rooms

name: Hunter College -- Thomas Hunter Hall
directions: The third floor of Thomas Hunter, near the club rooms.

name: Blue Hill Public Library
directions: One gender neutral bathroom in children's room on first floor of the library; two gender neutral bathrooms on the second floor just across from the elevator.
comment: All are always welcome in the library, even if it's just to use the bathroom. The upstairs bathroom on the right has a urinal in addition to a toilet, but both are marked and treated as gender neutral.

name: UCSF Library
directions: All bathroom libraries, including just to the right after you enter at the main front entrance.
comment: You do not have to have a UCSF ID to enter the library and use the bathrooms.

name: Margaret Jacks Hall, Building 460
directions: first floor, on the right as you cross the lobby from the main entrance

name: Margaret Jacks Hall, Building 460
directions: first floor, on the right as you cross the lobby from the main entrance

name: ONE National Gay and Lesbian Archives at the USC Libaries
comment: Bathrooms labeled as "Butch" and "Fabulous." Stay safe friends. Love you.

name: Beans & Cream Coffee House
directions: Near the back.
comment: I'm not sure if you "have" to be a paying customer but they are a locally owned business, so please be kind.

name: Target
directions: Near the front door- it's the family restroom.

name: University of Oregon, Erb Memorial Union
directions: On the ground floor, on the very northeastern tip. When you see the LGBTQA3 center, you're almost there. https://emu.uoregon.edu/map

name: Great Sage
directions: In back of restaurant.

name: No More Empty Pots
directions: There are two doors between the entry/conference area and the kitchen/office spaces.
comment: Good staff. Hours are irregular, but if they're around they'll let you in. Often there until late evening on weekdays.

name: Bryant Community Center, Community Action Network
directions: Through one of the two brown doors with toilet-shaped mirrors on them at the back of the main room, opposite the TV.
comment: The Bryant Community Center is a good space. Open most days, including weekends, from 9-6. If a staff member is around they will let you in.

name: The Box LA
directions: Located inside the art gallery. Open most Wednesdays through Saturdays, noon to 6pm.

name: Mark & Emily Turner Memorial Library
directions: All bathrooms. 2 located in children's section on 1st floor. 2 located on 2nd floor.

name: Hearth
directions: In the back of the cafe, on the left

name: The Discovery Museums
directions: Family Restrooms available, single stall

name: Kresge Town Hall
directions: To the left of Kresge's Owl's Nest Cafe.
comment: Generally accessible but campus is full of hills so could be more difficult depending on what direction you are coming from.

name: The Way Inn - gas station
directions: In the back left.
comment: Request the key at the counter, it is for paying customers officially but they won't mind anyone using it if they ask politely and say thank you.

name: Prairie State College
directions: 2nd floor at the southwest side of the building.

name: Compass Center
directions: First floor, volunteers will show you where
comment: CC warmly welcomes all identities!

name: Bonsai Brewing
comment: Single person bathrooms, one male one female.

name: Abernethy Hall
street: South Columbia Street and Cameron Avenue
directions: 1st floor by the stairs
comment: ALL are welcome :)

name: Third Street Market/Bookworks
directions: In the hallway between businesses

name: Montana Coffee Traders
directions: In the back

name: Loomis Laboratory of Physics
directions: Basement on East side of N-S hallway. Room 14.

name: G. G. Brown Building
directions: In between GGB and EECS, first floor of GGB.

name: Stephen Klein Wellness Center
directions: In lobby two on far end
comment: Free to public

name: Stones Throw Brewery
comment: Safe space no matter what :)

name: Southeastern Community College
directions: Near the southeast corner of Building 100 near business office

name: Lemon Street Market
directions:
appears to probably be accessible, but I can not confirm
first floor, past the produce
comment:
natural food market, kind staff
it is possible to use the facilities without purchase
they have a small parking lot too

name: SPACE Gallery
directions: There are two separate gender neutral bathrooms with stalls. One has a urinal. The sign on the outside of the bathrooms indicates that they are gender neutral and open to everyone.

name: Mountain View College
directions: West side of campus, W building, by room 168 (to the left of the staircase)
comment: no Automatic Door Button

name: Arch Street United Methodist Church
directions: Immediately to the left after entering through the Broad Street doors.
comment: This is a 100% LGBTQ affirming church and strives to be a refuge to anyone in need of one. Open all day Sunday, and 10 am to 3 pm weekdays, plus other varying times. The building is only wheelchair accessible if you ask for a staff member to set up the ramp on the front steps.
